1
00:00:06,718 --> 00:00:11,155
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,222 --> 00:00:14,749
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:14,826 --> 00:00:18,262
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,329 --> 00:00:21,924
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:21,999 --> 00:00:25,264
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,336 --> 00:00:27,270
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,073 --> 00:00:32,008
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,076 --> 00:00:35,876
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:43,118
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,354 --> 00:00:50,419
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:50,728 --> 00:00:56,860
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,001 --> 00:01:01,267
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,339 --> 00:01:04,934
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,009 --> 00:01:08,342
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,412 --> 00:01:12,041
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,116 --> 00:01:15,711
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:15,787 --> 00:01:19,279
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,357 --> 00:01:22,815
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,027 --> 00:01:27,123
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:34,415 --> 00:01:35,439
A hot spring?

21
00:01:35,583 --> 00:01:40,919
Yeah, just off of this road
there's a nice town with a hot spring.

22
00:01:41,622 --> 00:01:43,055
Yunosato Hot Springs...

23
00:01:43,725 --> 00:01:46,819
They say it does a world of good
for fatigue and beauty.

24
00:01:46,961 --> 00:01:50,920
Aren't we going straight home?
Everyone's waiting

25
00:01:51,032 --> 00:01:52,522
Naruto's right.

26
00:01:52,834 --> 00:01:54,631
Our hometown is in
a state of emergency,

27
00:01:54,702 --> 00:01:57,136
there's no time to procrastinate.

28
00:01:57,338 --> 00:02:00,569
It won't make much difference
if we're one or two days late...

29
00:02:02,977 --> 00:02:07,175
It's really popular with girls,
and it's mixed bathing...

30
00:02:09,751 --> 00:02:11,150
Hey?! Pervy Sage!?

31
00:02:12,587 --> 00:02:15,556
Sometimes it's necessary for humans
to take breathers.

32
00:02:15,790 --> 00:02:18,020
We'll take one bath!

33
00:02:18,359 --> 00:02:20,691
That's not what you said before!

34
00:02:20,962 --> 00:02:23,487
It's okay. Well, let's go!

35
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:34,231
That's her, no mistake.

36
00:02:34,709 --> 00:02:37,303
We've finally... found her.

37
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:43,784
<i>Kidnapped!</i>
<i>Naruto's Hot Spring Adventure!</i>

38
00:02:56,464 --> 00:02:59,399
We have the pleasure of
a visit from four people and one piglet.

39
00:02:59,667 --> 00:03:01,225
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

40
00:03:06,741 --> 00:03:09,266
Even though this has mixed bathing...

41
00:03:09,377 --> 00:03:13,677
I'm all alone with this brat.
I'm so unlucky.

42
00:03:14,382 --> 00:03:17,078
Well then, shall we play pachinko
or something?

43
00:03:17,151 --> 00:03:19,642
We have plenty of time before dinner.

44
00:03:20,021 --> 00:03:22,114
You're not going to the hot spring?

45
00:03:22,423 --> 00:03:24,357
If we go right now, there are fools...

46
00:03:24,425 --> 00:03:25,790
So, let's go, let's go.

47
00:03:34,535 --> 00:03:36,366
I'm going to get out already.

48
00:03:36,437 --> 00:03:40,032
Not yet, not yet.
Not until the girls get here.

49
00:03:40,474 --> 00:03:41,873
Oh, I see...

50
00:03:44,045 --> 00:03:46,673
Well, c'mon girls.
All of you, come on...

51
00:03:47,648 --> 00:03:49,047
Welcome!

52
00:03:49,617 --> 00:03:51,744
Ah, that was refreshing.

53
00:03:55,990 --> 00:03:57,423
W-We've been robbed!

54
00:04:00,828 --> 00:04:03,422
The necklace I got from
Old Lady Tsunade is gone!

55
00:04:04,498 --> 00:04:06,796
Where! Where is it?!

56
00:04:09,003 --> 00:04:11,938
"If you want your necklace back,
give back the money"?

57
00:04:12,406 --> 00:04:14,636
"Will wait at the three cedars on
the mountain behind."

58
00:04:14,709 --> 00:04:16,142
Signed, the Akagi Family.

59
00:04:17,211 --> 00:04:18,007
Money?

60
00:04:19,347 --> 00:04:20,871
What are they talking about?

61
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:24,347
Girls came in, all right.

62
00:04:25,052 --> 00:04:26,019
But...

63
00:04:28,222 --> 00:04:30,588
they're all female monkeys!

64
00:04:33,527 --> 00:04:35,552
I want to bathe with <i>people.</i>

65
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:41,594
Hey, here I am!

66
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:44,898
Come out! Akagi Family!

67
00:04:48,242 --> 00:04:49,607
What do you want, kid?!

68
00:04:50,311 --> 00:04:52,302
That's my line!

69
00:04:52,580 --> 00:04:55,743
I haven't borrowed any money
from you people!

70
00:04:56,017 --> 00:04:58,451
So give me my necklace back!

71
00:04:58,753 --> 00:05:00,186
"My" necklace?

72
00:05:00,988 --> 00:05:02,979
Did we mistake his stuff
for that woman's?

73
00:05:03,357 --> 00:05:04,949
Ah, that's it!
Give it back!

74
00:05:05,192 --> 00:05:06,318
W-Wait!

75
00:05:07,028 --> 00:05:08,586
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

76
00:05:09,931 --> 00:05:10,920
Go!

77
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,828
You thieves!

78
00:05:14,502 --> 00:05:16,367
- Take this!
- Go!

79
00:05:16,704 --> 00:05:17,534
H-Help...

80
00:05:20,174 --> 00:05:22,574
People came, all right...

81
00:05:24,478 --> 00:05:25,172
But...

82
00:05:26,013 --> 00:05:28,174
They're all men!

83
00:05:28,249 --> 00:05:30,080
- Bring it on!
- Cheers!

84
00:05:31,285 --> 00:05:33,310
I want to bathe with women...

85
00:05:36,357 --> 00:05:40,020
Huh? So the one who borrowed money
is Old Lady Tsunade?

86
00:05:40,294 --> 00:05:43,695
Yes... nicknamed
the Legendary Sitting Duck.

87
00:05:44,098 --> 00:05:46,999
She played at the Akagi gambling den
until she was penniless.

88
00:05:47,501 --> 00:05:49,526
We loaned her what she lost.

89
00:05:49,971 --> 00:05:52,166
That's right, and there's an I.O.U.

90
00:05:55,109 --> 00:05:58,943
Wha?! There are so many zeros!

91
00:05:59,413 --> 00:06:02,439
I'm Senta, this guy is called Bunzo.

92
00:06:03,851 --> 00:06:07,878
The boss ordered us to collect
on the debt three years ago...

93
00:06:12,226 --> 00:06:14,956
We set out on a journey
from Akagi Mountain

94
00:06:15,029 --> 00:06:17,725
prepared not to return
until we get the money back.

95
00:06:19,266 --> 00:06:22,429
We've heard rumors about
the lady here and there...

96
00:06:23,137 --> 00:06:24,627
But, she sure was something

97
00:06:24,705 --> 00:06:28,664
She was elusive and quite hard to find.

98
00:06:30,311 --> 00:06:35,374
Then recently, we caught
some information that she'd appeared.

99
00:06:36,283 --> 00:06:38,979
We were waiting on
the side of the road...

100
00:06:39,987 --> 00:06:43,479
That's when we came along
with Old Lady Tsunade.

101
00:06:44,158 --> 00:06:47,787
But why did you raid the room
so stealthily?

102
00:06:47,995 --> 00:06:49,292
Rumor has it that

103
00:06:49,363 --> 00:06:52,025
that ordinary means don't work
against the Legendary Sitting Duck.

104
00:06:52,099 --> 00:06:54,192
We didn't think that
if we tried to collect amicably,

105
00:06:54,268 --> 00:06:55,997
she would pay us.

106
00:06:56,337 --> 00:06:57,668
She's certainly stingy...

107
00:06:58,305 --> 00:07:01,866
We heard that she cherished the necklace
next to her life,

108
00:07:01,942 --> 00:07:04,672
so we thought she'd pay
in exchange for it.

109
00:07:04,945 --> 00:07:08,244
No way. After all, you raided <i>my</i> room.

110
00:07:08,783 --> 00:07:13,618
We never even dreamed that the owner
of the necklace would have changed...

111
00:07:14,655 --> 00:07:19,649
Err... Can't you ask the lady to pay?

112
00:07:19,894 --> 00:07:22,795
Uh, even you say so...

113
00:07:22,997 --> 00:07:26,194
Please! If we don't get the money back,
we can't go home!

114
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:28,699
Our wives and kids are waiting for us
to come home!

115
00:07:29,603 --> 00:07:32,333
- Please... I'm begging you!
- Please... I'm begging you!

116
00:07:39,346 --> 00:07:41,075
It's all gone...

117
00:07:41,215 --> 00:07:44,776
Bad luck...
Darn it. I'm stone broke.

118
00:07:44,852 --> 00:07:47,150
Well, let's call it quits with pachinko.

119
00:07:47,221 --> 00:07:48,586
It's about time for a bath...

120
00:07:48,656 --> 00:07:49,953
- Shizune...
- Yes?

121
00:07:50,291 --> 00:07:52,691
My bag is at the front desk of the inn.

122
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:56,924
What?!
Y-You can't mean to bring it here?!

123
00:07:57,098 --> 00:07:59,123
Everything to your name is in it...

124
00:08:00,334 --> 00:08:03,826
I've just lost! I can't repress this feeling!

125
00:08:04,271 --> 00:08:06,136
Just bring it without complaint.

126
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:08,208
Yes, ma'am!

127
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,846
Huh? Could you be...

128
00:08:15,216 --> 00:08:17,309
Y-You are...!

129
00:08:19,053 --> 00:08:21,146
There are women, all right...

130
00:08:24,358 --> 00:08:25,222
But...

131
00:08:31,198 --> 00:08:34,167
I was hoping for younger,
more titillating women...

132
00:08:36,804 --> 00:08:37,964
This one, right?

133
00:08:38,439 --> 00:08:39,098
Thank you...

134
00:08:40,174 --> 00:08:41,766
Are you with Ms. Tsunade?

135
00:08:42,343 --> 00:08:43,105
Yes.

136
00:08:43,711 --> 00:08:45,906
This came for her not long ago...

137
00:08:46,747 --> 00:08:48,908
<i>To Tsunade</i>
<i>A letter? I wonder who could've...?</i>

138
00:08:53,921 --> 00:08:55,923
Lady Tsunade! Lady Tsunade!

139
00:08:55,923 --> 00:08:57,720
Lady Tsunade!

140
00:08:58,159 --> 00:09:00,559
Huh? Lady Tsunade!

141
00:09:02,897 --> 00:09:03,829
She's not here...

142
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,697
Okay, Tonton...

143
00:09:07,935 --> 00:09:10,631
You know to search for
Lady Tsunade, right!

144
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:18,742
What, impossible? Why?

145
00:09:20,147 --> 00:09:23,742
I see! The smell of the sulfur
from the hot spring interferes...

146
00:09:24,185 --> 00:09:26,619
Well then, the only way
to search for her is on foot!

147
00:09:27,054 --> 00:09:28,419
Lady Tsunade!

148
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:31,950
Lady Tsunade! Lady Tsunade!

149
00:09:33,027 --> 00:09:36,087
Lady Tsunade! Lady Tsunade!

150
00:09:36,931 --> 00:09:38,398
Where are you!

151
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:40,323
We have a problem!

152
00:09:40,401 --> 00:09:42,426
Lady Tsunade!

153
00:09:46,907 --> 00:09:48,932
Oh, what in the world should I do?

154
00:09:49,877 --> 00:09:52,038
<i>We have Naruto Uzumaki.</i>

155
00:09:52,179 --> 00:09:55,410
<i>If you want him returned unharmed,</i>
<i>please return all of the money you owe!</i>

156
00:09:55,549 --> 00:09:58,985
<i>We'll wait by the three cedars on</i>
<i>the mountain behind. The Akagi Family</i>

157
00:09:59,386 --> 00:10:02,082
What should I do?
I have to help Naruto.

158
00:10:02,456 --> 00:10:05,721
On top of that, if it's discovered
that Lady Tsunade has a huge debt,

159
00:10:06,093 --> 00:10:09,859
talk of her installment as
the Fifth Hokage will probably end.

160
00:10:12,399 --> 00:10:15,459
That's right, we have
to handle this by ourselves.

161
00:10:16,303 --> 00:10:17,600
Right, Tonton?

162
00:10:23,911 --> 00:10:25,674
Do you think it's going to work out well?

163
00:10:25,879 --> 00:10:27,369
No problem.

164
00:10:27,648 --> 00:10:28,876
Here she comes.

165
00:10:34,488 --> 00:10:35,785
Old Lady Tsunade!

166
00:10:35,923 --> 00:10:36,719
Stop!

167
00:10:37,891 --> 00:10:40,291
You know who we are, right?

168
00:10:41,061 --> 00:10:42,790
You're the henchmen of the Akagi.

169
00:10:43,297 --> 00:10:44,992
Then I'll make it brief.

170
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:48,793
Pay back your debt
in one lump sum.

171
00:10:49,136 --> 00:10:50,626
Or else...

172
00:10:51,705 --> 00:10:53,502
his life is over!

173
00:10:54,475 --> 00:10:56,534
Help me!

174
00:10:56,877 --> 00:11:00,313
Whatever.
His life doesn't matter much to me.

175
00:11:00,381 --> 00:11:02,178
- Huh!
- What did you just say?!

176
00:11:02,650 --> 00:11:04,515
Well then, the money...

177
00:11:08,255 --> 00:11:10,553
Why did it come to this?

178
00:11:11,191 --> 00:11:14,490
This isn't titillating
this is just tight!

179
00:11:19,099 --> 00:11:22,535
<i>Drats! Let me have patience!</i>

180
00:11:26,541 --> 00:11:27,974
Didn't you hear me?

181
00:11:28,243 --> 00:11:31,644
It doesn't matter to me
what happens with his life.

182
00:11:32,180 --> 00:11:34,705
You... darn old hag!

183
00:11:34,783 --> 00:11:38,344
Was what I would have said,
until just a little bit ago, I think.

184
00:11:39,988 --> 00:11:42,923
Once I become the Hokage,
he'd be a precious subordinate.

185
00:11:43,358 --> 00:11:45,053
I can't leave him in the mess.

186
00:11:46,795 --> 00:11:48,490
Old Lady Tsunade...

187
00:11:48,930 --> 00:11:53,128
Right now, this is all I've got.
Take it.

188
00:11:57,872 --> 00:11:59,897
Let me make sure of this.

189
00:12:03,978 --> 00:12:08,244
I don't mean it's paid off in full,
but that'll do it for the interest, right?

190
00:12:16,391 --> 00:12:17,585
Fake!

191
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:26,723
You're not going to pay
the money back?

192
00:12:27,402 --> 00:12:28,960
It's none of your business.

193
00:12:29,104 --> 00:12:32,904
These guys can't go home!
Don't you feel sorry for them!

194
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:34,842
You couldn't possibly?

195
00:12:34,909 --> 00:12:37,776
In that case, I'll have to use force
to get it back!

196
00:12:40,915 --> 00:12:42,280
Naruto's Shadow Clones?!

197
00:12:43,785 --> 00:12:47,186
<i>I see, Naruto has joined hands</i>
<i>with the Akagi Family...</i>

198
00:12:47,355 --> 00:12:49,823
<i>So, where did Naruto and company go?</i>

199
00:12:52,794 --> 00:12:53,920
As expected...

200
00:12:54,429 --> 00:12:56,795
I didn't think she'd hand
the money over meekly.

201
00:12:56,865 --> 00:12:58,196
But to be that much of a coward...

202
00:12:58,533 --> 00:12:59,864
What should we do?

203
00:13:00,135 --> 00:13:02,660
Old Lady Tsunade has a huge suitcase.

204
00:13:03,238 --> 00:13:05,433
No doubt there's money in it.

205
00:13:05,874 --> 00:13:09,002
We have to do something
to get our hands on that suitcase.

206
00:13:17,819 --> 00:13:19,047
Shoot!

207
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:22,612
I'm supposed to be kidnapped,
and she's casually drinking <i>sake.</i>

208
00:13:23,324 --> 00:13:24,621
It's that suitcase.

209
00:13:25,260 --> 00:13:26,887
How do we get it out?

210
00:13:27,328 --> 00:13:29,262
Leave it to me.

211
00:13:33,701 --> 00:13:36,499
Lady Tsunade, you've returned.

212
00:13:36,704 --> 00:13:40,196
Ah, here's the suitcase.

213
00:13:40,275 --> 00:13:43,267
It's dangerous,
so let's leave it at the front desk.

214
00:13:43,411 --> 00:13:44,571
Well then...

215
00:14:01,062 --> 00:14:03,121
Look, I went and got it!

216
00:14:03,331 --> 00:14:04,559
- You did it!
- You did it!

217
00:14:09,237 --> 00:14:10,465
Old Lady Tsunade!

218
00:14:11,873 --> 00:14:14,808
Shoot... If you're the Hokage...

219
00:14:16,344 --> 00:14:17,208
If you're the Hokage,

220
00:14:17,278 --> 00:14:20,577
then pay your debt back
like a Hokage would!

221
00:14:21,249 --> 00:14:23,843
A Hokage is meant
to protect everyone!

222
00:14:24,486 --> 00:14:27,421
These guys can't return their home,
they are desperate!

223
00:14:27,789 --> 00:14:29,086
Why don't you do something?!

224
00:14:29,858 --> 00:14:30,916
Naruto...

225
00:14:30,992 --> 00:14:34,450
Or do people from other countries
not matter to you?

226
00:14:34,529 --> 00:14:37,828
That kind of Hokage...
I cannot accept!

227
00:14:39,601 --> 00:14:40,329
Now!

228
00:14:44,105 --> 00:14:44,799
Here!

229
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,702
Hurry up and run away!

230
00:14:46,841 --> 00:14:47,808
- Right!
- Okay!

231
00:14:59,053 --> 00:15:01,317
Oh, she's already catching up!

232
00:15:02,090 --> 00:15:03,387
It's all or nothing!

233
00:15:07,028 --> 00:15:07,756
Huh?

234
00:15:07,962 --> 00:15:09,190
- You did it!
- You did it!

235
00:15:12,433 --> 00:15:13,457
Tonton?!

236
00:15:13,868 --> 00:15:14,664
Naruto!

237
00:15:15,837 --> 00:15:19,136
Just hand over the suitcase! Or else!

238
00:15:19,507 --> 00:15:20,940
F-Fork over the suitcase!

239
00:15:26,047 --> 00:15:28,515
If we take a direct hit from
Old Lady Tsunade's attack,

240
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:30,050
then it's over!

241
00:15:31,886 --> 00:15:32,944
Out of the way, out of the way!

242
00:15:33,054 --> 00:15:33,884
Purse snatchers?

243
00:15:34,255 --> 00:15:35,313
Excuse us!

244
00:15:35,390 --> 00:15:36,357
Hey what's going on?!

245
00:15:36,491 --> 00:15:39,722
Hey! Don't cause trouble
for the general public!

246
00:15:39,794 --> 00:15:42,957
It's because you're following us!

247
00:15:45,266 --> 00:15:46,858
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

248
00:15:55,877 --> 00:15:57,208
Shadow Clone Jutsu!

249
00:16:08,323 --> 00:16:09,722
What's going on...?

250
00:16:10,325 --> 00:16:13,055
Naruto, we leave it up to you.

251
00:16:14,329 --> 00:16:15,421
<i>This is no good.</i>

252
00:16:15,496 --> 00:16:17,123
<i>If the contents of that suitcase</i>
<i>become known,</i>

253
00:16:17,198 --> 00:16:18,495
<i>it will be a disaster...</i>

254
00:16:21,869 --> 00:16:24,269
That's right, that happened too.

255
00:16:24,505 --> 00:16:26,769
And I was young then too.

256
00:16:27,675 --> 00:16:29,267
Gulp it down.

257
00:16:31,212 --> 00:16:32,770
Excuse me, Boss.

258
00:16:33,081 --> 00:16:35,675
What is it? You're in front of a guest.

259
00:16:35,984 --> 00:16:37,110
W-Well...

260
00:16:48,329 --> 00:16:49,318
<i>A clone!</i>

261
00:16:54,836 --> 00:16:56,167
<i>That's a clone too?</i>

262
00:17:01,743 --> 00:17:02,835
<i>Wrong again.</i>

263
00:17:07,115 --> 00:17:08,878
Sheesh, which is the real one?!

264
00:17:13,354 --> 00:17:14,321
The rest...

265
00:17:15,189 --> 00:17:16,781
- Where are the rest?!
- Where are the rest?!

266
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,600
Over there!

267
00:17:37,612 --> 00:17:39,546
- Hold it!
- Hold it!

268
00:17:42,984 --> 00:17:44,042
- Naruto!
- Naruto!

269
00:17:44,819 --> 00:17:47,788
- Wait!
- Wait!

270
00:17:50,558 --> 00:17:51,718
- Naruto!
- Naruto!

271
00:17:55,096 --> 00:17:56,358
Prepare yourself!

272
00:18:06,541 --> 00:18:08,202
Shoot, let me go! Let me go!

273
00:18:08,376 --> 00:18:09,502
Settle down!

274
00:18:12,747 --> 00:18:14,339
G-Got it!

275
00:18:14,515 --> 00:18:15,482
The money!

276
00:18:16,217 --> 00:18:17,809
Okay, they got it!

277
00:18:23,858 --> 00:18:24,950
IOU's?!

278
00:18:25,059 --> 00:18:26,321
It's not money?!

279
00:18:27,562 --> 00:18:30,053
- Oh no...
- This is too much!

280
00:18:30,331 --> 00:18:33,300
What are you doing?!
This is in the middle of town!

281
00:18:33,601 --> 00:18:34,329
Huh!

282
00:18:36,204 --> 00:18:40,072
T-Two Old Ladies?!

283
00:18:40,274 --> 00:18:42,765
You're mixed up in
this commotion as well?

284
00:18:43,177 --> 00:18:45,441
I'd like to hear your reason
for it, Shizune!

285
00:18:48,349 --> 00:18:50,817
Hello... Lady Tsunade...

286
00:18:50,985 --> 00:18:52,885
What?! Shizune...

287
00:18:53,254 --> 00:18:55,814
And you guys belong to the Akagi.

288
00:18:55,990 --> 00:18:58,049
B-Boss Jirocho!

289
00:18:58,392 --> 00:18:59,324
Who?

290
00:18:59,494 --> 00:19:00,586
You don't know?!

291
00:19:00,795 --> 00:19:04,424
He's the number one gang boss,
Jirocho from the Land of Tea!

292
00:19:04,932 --> 00:19:06,729
He's an old friend of mine.

293
00:19:07,368 --> 00:19:09,563
As luck would have it,
we met by accident on the street.

294
00:19:09,971 --> 00:19:12,405
You're Bunzo and Senta
if I'm not mistaken.

295
00:19:13,274 --> 00:19:15,868
Just in time.
I have something to say to you!

296
00:19:18,246 --> 00:19:19,645
- What?!
- What?!

297
00:19:20,214 --> 00:19:22,546
You mean the debt to the Akagi Family?

298
00:19:23,151 --> 00:19:24,880
I paid it back a year ago.

299
00:19:25,953 --> 00:19:27,648
Is that true?

300
00:19:28,289 --> 00:19:30,314
That was last year,
when we were near Akagi's.

301
00:19:30,892 --> 00:19:32,450
Did you forget?

302
00:19:32,593 --> 00:19:34,060
I-I'm sorry.

303
00:19:34,495 --> 00:19:35,052
Hey!

304
00:19:35,963 --> 00:19:38,158
It's a circular from Akagi
addressed to me.

305
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:41,201
I'll just read the part addressed to you.

306
00:19:41,936 --> 00:19:43,927
"Senta and Bunzo,

307
00:19:44,438 --> 00:19:48,169
"The debt is paid, come home soon."
Signed, Shugoro Akagi.

308
00:19:48,843 --> 00:19:49,502
See?

309
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:53,645
You've gotta be kidding.

310
00:19:55,783 --> 00:19:57,751
All that energy spent, for nothing.

311
00:19:59,954 --> 00:20:02,184
- Thank you for helping us.
- Thank you for helping us.

312
00:20:03,324 --> 00:20:06,088
- Now we can go home relieved.
- Now we can go home relieved.

313
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:08,191
Go in good spirits.

314
00:20:08,629 --> 00:20:11,564
- You too, Naruto. Take care!
- You too, Naruto. Take care!

315
00:20:12,099 --> 00:20:15,034
Hey, if the suitcase
doesn't have money in it,

316
00:20:15,102 --> 00:20:17,696
why were you so serious
about getting it back?

317
00:20:17,805 --> 00:20:18,772
That's...

318
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:23,138
If the IOU's were discovered
by the people in the village,

319
00:20:23,377 --> 00:20:27,245
they'll oppose Lady Tsunade's
installment as Hokage

320
00:20:28,015 --> 00:20:29,949
You worry too much.

321
00:20:30,551 --> 00:20:32,712
The Hokage and the debt
are unrelated.

322
00:20:32,820 --> 00:20:35,448
Not only that,
she said she returned the money,

323
00:20:35,656 --> 00:20:37,715
so there's nothing to worry about.

324
00:20:38,326 --> 00:20:40,157
At least the Akagi debt was...

325
00:20:40,394 --> 00:20:41,122
What?

326
00:20:41,195 --> 00:20:42,958
Don't worry, don't worry!

327
00:20:45,032 --> 00:20:46,863
What? We forgot something?

328
00:20:56,143 --> 00:20:59,112
Finally, the time has come.

329
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:01,710
Communal bathing with girls...

330
00:21:01,949 --> 00:21:04,611
Patience paid off...

331
00:21:06,254 --> 00:21:10,953
<i>I believe your promise,</i>
<i>its a true heart give me courage</i>

332
00:21:11,025 --> 00:21:15,359
<i>Always I feel it</i>
<i>the precious time with you</i>

333
00:21:15,963 --> 00:21:19,490
<i>On your still shoulder</i>

334
00:21:20,735 --> 00:21:25,195
<i>I feel the wind that blows</i>
<i>towards tomorrow</i>

335
00:21:25,373 --> 00:21:30,811
<i>The city lights are like pieces of stars</i>

336
00:21:31,312 --> 00:21:35,612
<i>That hold us together</i>

337
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:45,321
<i>"Each one of us glows differently,"</i>

338
00:21:45,393 --> 00:21:47,987
<i>you say laughingly</i>

339
00:21:48,229 --> 00:21:53,895
<i>but you look most dazzling</i>

340
00:21:54,468 --> 00:21:58,837
<i>Like a comet,</i>

341
00:21:58,906 --> 00:22:05,004
<i>like the rainbow after the storm</i>

342
00:22:05,079 --> 00:22:12,178
<i>You bring light into my heart</i>

343
00:22:13,187 --> 00:22:22,562
<i>Being lost can be the answer</i>

344
00:22:23,898 --> 00:22:31,430
<i>Let's promise we won't cheat</i>

345
00:22:31,505 --> 00:22:35,498
<i>Uh...like a shooting star,</i>
<i>we do go ahead.</i>

346
00:22:38,346 --> 00:22:39,779
You're awesome,
Old Lady Tsunade!

347
00:22:39,847 --> 00:22:42,372
Kakashi Sensei and Sasuke
are all right now!

348
00:22:42,450 --> 00:22:44,281
You can't rejoice yet.

349
00:22:44,418 --> 00:22:47,251
The current situation
in the village is serious.

350
00:22:47,388 --> 00:22:48,650
You're right.
I have to do my best,

351
00:22:48,723 --> 00:22:50,088
And work hard for
the village as well.

352
00:22:50,825 --> 00:22:53,020
Hey! N-Naruto,
where do you think you're going?!

353
00:22:53,094 --> 00:22:54,959
I have to fill my stomach first!

354
00:22:55,096 --> 00:22:57,758
You have no sense of emergency...

355
00:22:58,065 --> 00:23:01,193
Next time: "Tsunade's Warning
Ninja No More!"

356
00:23:01,602 --> 00:23:03,866
What is that supposed to mean?!
